      "side": 1,
      "message": "this functions currently has two responsibilities:\n1) batching, i.e. splitting a slice of test results into a slice of slices of test results\n2) preparation of the invocation containing one batch\n\nthe consequence is that we have an extra type, testResultBatch, which doesn\u0027t really have to exist. I think it would be simpler if we employed SRP here:\n\n  func batchTestResults(ctx context.Context, trs []*pb.TestResult, batchSize int) [][]*pb.TestResult\n\nthen a loop over results of this func. In each iteration we create a containing inv and insert it. Then we don\u0027t need aux func like ToMutations here.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 5,
